               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Maṣḥafa gǝnzat “Book of the Funeral Ritual” (fols. 3ra-124va)&#xD; -
                     Discourse of St Athanasius on death (fols. 3ra-9va)&#xD; - Maṣḥaf za-waḍʾāt
                     ʾǝm-ʾIyārusalem “Book that Came from Jerusalem” (fols. 9va-17rb)&#xD; - Lǝfāfa
                     ṣǝdq “Bandlet of Righteousness” (fols. 17rb-20rb)&#xD; - Mangada samāy “Journey
                     to Heaven” (fols. 20rb-21ra)&#xD; - Introduction (fols. 21ra-23rb)&#xD; -
                     Antiphons (kǝśtat, mawāśǝʾt and mǝlṭān with Musical notation) (fols. 27vb-28ra;
                     45va-vb; 49vb-50ra; 51va-vb, 57rb, 58vb-59ra; 61va-vb; 123ra-124va)&#xD; -
                     Homily by St Jacob of Serug for the funeral of priests and deacons (fols.
                     66rb-79rb)&#xD; - Homily by ʾabbā Salāmā, Metropolitan of Ethiopia (fols.
                     83rb-87vb)&#xD; &#xD; Additio 1.</summary>
